<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holmb., Bot. Not. 1924: 326" authorityYear="1924" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus lepidus" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lepidus">Bromus lepidus</taxonomicName>
Holmb., Bot. Not. 1924: 326 (1924).Type Protologue: &quot;Nach ROUY kommt sie in Frankreich hier und da vor,aber ziemlich selten; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Krösche">Kroesche</normalizedToken>
hat sie nur von einem 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ståndort">Standort</normalizedToken>
in Norddeutschland. In Schweden kommt sie besonders in Schonen vor; ich habe sie mehrmals eingesammelt, wie in der Gegend von Lund und 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Malmö">Malmoe</normalizedToken>
an mehreren Orten; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Svenshög">Svenshoeg</normalizedToken>
in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Wallkärra">Wallkaerra</normalizedToken>
; Skartofta in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Öved">Oeved</normalizedToken>
; Gudmundtorp. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Außerdem">Ausserdem</normalizedToken>
sah ich Exemplare aus 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Blommeröd">Blommeroed</normalizedToken>
in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Öved">Oeved</normalizedToken>
(leg. P. Boren 1903), Skelderviken (leg. Sten Selander), Kalmar (leg. N. Blomgren), 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Borås">Boras</normalizedToken>
(leg. C. Sandberg), Fyen, Stenlose (leg. G. Samuelsson). Kommt in Klee- und Grasfeldern, auf Rainen, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Wegrändern">Wegraendern</normalizedToken>
etc. vor, oft mit 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. mollis" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">B. mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. commutatus" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="commutatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">B. commutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
zusammen; bei 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Malmö">Malmoe</normalizedToken>
auch als Ruderat&quot;. Type: SWEDEN. Scania: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Malmö">Malmoe</normalizedToken>
, in ruderatis, 18-06-1920, Otto R.Holmberg, (lectotype, designated here: LD [LD1136595 image!]; isolectotype: K [K000913599!]). (Figure 7)
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="60">
<taxonomicName authority="Holmb." authorityName="Holmb" authorityYear="1924" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" form="lasiolepis" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="f." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus lepidus" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="lepidus">
<pageBreakToken pageId="7" pageNumber="60" start="start">Bromus</pageBreakToken>
lepidus Holmb. f. lasiolepis
</taxonomicName>
Holmb., Bot. Not. 1924: 326 (1924). Type Protologue: not indicated. Type: Sweden. Scania: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Vallkörra">Vallkoerra</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Svenenshög">Svenenshoeg</normalizedToken>
. 4-07-1923. Otto R.Holmberg, (lectotype, designated here: LD [LD 1136235 image!]; isolectotype: K [K000913598!]). (Figure 8)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="60" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="60">
This taxon has a long history full of nomenclatural problems. 
<bibRefCitation author="Duval-Jouve, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="196 - 211" refId="B9" refString="Duval-Jouve, MJ, 1865. Variations paralelles des types congeneres. Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France 12 (4): 196 - 211" title="Variations paralelles des types congeneres." volume="12" year="1865">Duval-Jouve (1865</bibRefCitation>
: 208), who only lists, without naming them, the variations in spikelet size and hairiness of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Bromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, e.g. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus mollis" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Bromus mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="microstachys" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microstachys">microstachys</taxonomicName>
glabre&quot; and 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus mollis" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Bromus mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="microstachys" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microstachys">microstachys</taxonomicName>
pubescent&quot;. This is the first mention of this taxon. Later 
<bibRefCitation author="Rouy, GCH" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B26" refString="Rouy, GCH, 1913. Flore de France XIV. M.M. Deslis freres, Paris. http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=876&amp;Pagina=1" title="Flore de France XIV. M. M. Deslis freres, Paris. http: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / spa / Libro. php? Libro = 876 &amp; Pagina = 1" year="1913">Rouy (1913</bibRefCitation>
: 236) proposed a named variety under the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="W.D.J.Koch, 1844 (Parl.)" authorityName="W.D.J.Koch, 1844 (Parl.)" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Serrafalcus" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Serrafalcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Parl.: 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. mollis" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">S. mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="ß">ss</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="microstachys" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" rank="species" species="microstachys">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">microstachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rouy, giving &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus microstachys" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microstachys">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Bromus microstachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Duval-Jouve, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="196 - 211" refId="B9" refString="Duval-Jouve, MJ, 1865. Variations paralelles des types congeneres. Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France 12 (4): 196 - 211" title="Variations paralelles des types congeneres." volume="12" year="1865">Duval-Jouve&quot; (1865</bibRefCitation>
: 207) as a synonym and adding a diagnosis. Therefore, there is no doubt this is the same plant cited by Duval-Jouve (l. c.). Afterwards, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kroesche, E" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" pagination="329 - 332" refId="B19" refString="Kroesche, E, 1924. Neue Arten und Formen aus Nordwest-Deutschland. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 19: 329 - 332" title="Neue Arten und Formen aus Nordwest-Deutschland." volume="19" year="1924">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Krösche">Kroesche</normalizedToken>
(1924
</bibRefCitation>
: 329) described 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. gracilis" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">B. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Krösche">Kroesche</normalizedToken>
, which unfortunately is a posterior homonym as 
<bibRefCitation author="Weigel, CE" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Botany, British and Foreign" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B34" refString="Weigel, CE, 1772. Observationes Botanicae. Ant. Ferd. Roese. Gryphiae. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.123718" title="Observationes Botanicae. Ant. Ferd. Roese. Gryphiae. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 123718" year="1772">Weigel (1772</bibRefCitation>
: 15) previously proposed this name for a different plant.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="60">
Finally, 
<bibRefCitation author="Holmberg, OR" journalOrPublisher="Botaniska Notiser" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="313 - 328" refId="B14" refString="Holmberg, OR, 1924. Bromi molles, eine nomenklatorische und systematische Untersuchung. Botaniska Notiser 1924: 313 - 328" title="Bromi molles, eine nomenklatorische und systematische Untersuchung." volume="1924" year="1924">Holmberg (1924</bibRefCitation>
: 326) solves this unfortunate situation and names simultaneously the new taxa 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holmb., Bot. Not. 1924: 326" authorityYear="1924" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus lepidus" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lepidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Bromus lepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Holmb. and 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" form="lasiolepis" genus="B." infraspecific-rank="f." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. lepidus" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" rank="form" species="lepidus">B. lepidus f. lasiolepis</taxonomicName>
Holmb. The herbaria having Holmberg material are K, LD and S. There are 13 sheets in LD collected before 1924, five in S and three in K. It is reasonably certain that Holmberg studied all those plants before the description of the species and form and that all of them are original material. Therefore, we decided to limit our choices to sheets with the annotations &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. lepidus" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" rank="species" species="lepidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">B. lepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mihi&quot; and &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" form="lasiolepis" genus="B." infraspecific-rank="f." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. lepidus" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" rank="form" species="lepidus">B. lepidus f. lasiolepis</taxonomicName>
Holmb.&quot;, as this annotation indicates that Holmberg is interpreting them as the new taxa he is going to describe.
</paragraph>
